      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SNIPER'S SON (2) settled close last start and got the job done, winning by 1.3L over this trip at Belmont when on the quick turnaround. This looks to set up similarly and he only rises 1kg after the claim of Riordan. Can bring up back-to-back wins. SESH (5) couldn't make it a hat-trick at Belmont last start but he wasn't disgraced in defeat. He's trending the right way and he looks to get all the favours again here. Can get back to winning ways. ADMIRE THE GIRL (4) tackled a stronger race before the break in a race that turned out to be a strong form reference. Pike sticks from her latest trial and she profiles as a very progressive talent on the rise. Tongue tie and crossover go on now and she can return with a bang. SOMETHING ROYAL (8) is better than she showed last start and she can't be discounted. CAPITOLA (1) is ticking along nicely and can't be left out of calculations in this suitable event.",
